<div id="review_1335644" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1335644" />
    <a title="Nadiah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/91211-nadiah"><img alt="Nadiah" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1335644?book_show_action=true">May 21, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nadiah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nadiah" href="/user/show/91211-nadiah">Nadiah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780385407694" href="/book/show/264320.The_Mistress_Of_Spices">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91211-nadiah?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1335644" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13962876758967599909">As a big fan of Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni, I collect many of her books. The ones I have read are The Unknown Errors of Our Lives, Arranged Married, and the last one is The Mistress of Spices.<br/><br/>Like in her other books, in The Mistress of Spices, Divakaruni uses her beautiful writing style. Soft, unhurried, strong. She makes readers captivated in such a way that you feel every single sensation the main character, Tilo, undergoes.<br/><br/>This novel is somehow a flight of imagination, yet Divakaruni helps yo</span>
  <span id="freeText13962876758967599909" style="display:none">As a big fan of Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni, I collect many of her books. The ones I have read are The Unknown Errors of Our Lives, Arranged Married, and the last one is The Mistress of Spices.<br /><br />Like in her other books, in The Mistress of Spices, Divakaruni uses her beautiful writing style. Soft, unhurried, strong. She makes readers captivated in such a way that you feel every single sensation the main character, Tilo, undergoes.<br /><br />This novel is somehow a flight of imagination, yet Divakaruni helps you keep your feet on the ground. Both Ravenâ€”lover of Tiloâ€”and Tilo, they have a certain power, an inhuman one, yet they are humanized by the humane love they feel for each other.<br /><br />Not only the style and the plot can make readers unwilling to put the book down, but also the beautiful phrases.<br /><br />"Hope not built on reason brings disappointment only."<br /><br />"I tell myself, I deserve dignity, I deserve happiness."<br /><br />This novel has been filmed. I wonder if the movie has the same magical raptness as the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13962876758967599909" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


