  <span id="freeText4846814983754385685" style="display:none">The author built the world of the spices beautifully. The air of mystery and aura of foreboding gave chills through the beginning parts of the book. That's why it was surprising that the book turned on its head and took a somewhat 'filmy' turn. It seemed like towards the end, everything worked our easily and conveniently for the protagonist, despite it being against the philosophy and working of the spices-world. I still give it three stars because of Divakaruni's sheer power of creativity and description.</span>
